story.title: Our Little Secret - Part 1
story.storyDescription: Sometimes, it's hard to tell the difference between keeping a secret and telling a lie.
story.prePaywallNotification: WHAT?! Why is Jesse on the news? Keep reading OUR LITTLE SECRET to find out.
story.postPaywallNotification: OMG! What if Kat gets pinned for Jesse’s crime?! Click OUR LITTLE SECRET for the next episode.

messages.text: If she calls, don’t pick up.
I won't be at school today.
I saw something I wasn't supposed to…
Wait...the cops just came into class.
No matter what they tell you...
Haven’t heard from you in a while.
I know I’ve been super MIA but –
I really need my best friend right now.
We haven’t spoken in months, Kat.
I’m so sorry. It’s totally my fault.
I really need your help Em. You’re the only person I can trust.
Even when you piss me off ;)
Did you see the cops at school earlier today?
Shut up. Are you kidding me?
Em I’m worried it’s serious this time.
Something to do with his psycho stepmom…
What’s she got to do with it?
He said if she called me…I shouldn’t believe her.
But the cops are looking for HIM, no?
Idk…I mean yes, technically they are.
Kat. What do you want me to say?
You know how I feel about Jesse .
I know you’ve never approved of him…
And I’m sorry that’s put distance between us.
It’s not just about my approval!
But at least ADMIT that he’s always creating drama in your life.
I know Jesse’s been in trouble before.
But it’s never really been super serious.
How about the time he gave that kid Tony a bloody nose?
What about that time he went aggro on Mr. Grayson in English class?
And the time he got caught stealing milk from the corner store?
Everybody knows that the dude who owns that corner store hates Jesse.
Nobody ever says that part out loud, though.
Em you have NO IDEA what it’s like to be him.
To look like him in this town.
Guys at school giving him crap all the time.
Strangers giving him all kinds of side eye.
I didn’t believe it until I started seeing it myself.
Kat are you watching TV right now?
No…I went for a walk to get some fresh air.
They’re talking about his little sister…
The police have no idea where she is.
Jesse and I took her to the park.
His stepmom is sobbing on TV.
Oh god she looks SO sad.
That’s like, a mom’s worst nightmare.
That’s why the cops were looking for Jesse.
Do you think he had something to do with it??
He would never ever hurt Jenny.
She’s the only real family he’s got.
The cops probably just want to see if he knows anything…
They’re saying she disappeared from the house without a trace.
She’s so tiny in her school picture!
Jesse is going to be devastated.
Jesse vowed to take care of Jenny.
This has to be some kind of crazy mistake.
He’s making it worse, you know. Disappearing like that.
Makes everything look so much more suspicious…
She’s got to be somewhere nearby.
I don’t have a lot of time.
I’m going to the police station.
Kat - you know I would never hurt Jenny right?
You’re like the sweetest brother ever.
If anyone asks, we were together last night.
That’s what I’m telling the police.
I need you to say that too, ok?
Are you asking me to lie?
It’s not a lie. It’s more like, a secret.
This way, we’re both covered and my stepmom can’t pin this on me.
Your stepmom? Pin what on you?
Our alibi will get me out of questioning.
And then I can tell you everything.
I don’t want to lie to the cops Jesse.
But he says he’s going to the police.
Does he know anything about his sister?
He wants me to cover for him.
But he wants me to tell the cops we were together last night
You know you can’t do that right?
Lying to the cops is a CRIME.
I don’t know what to think right now.
You need to tell the cops the TRUTH.
You were not with Jesse last night.
Katherine if you’re there, please answer me.
Em – it’s exactly what Jesse was afraid of!!
What do you think she wants??
I desperately need your help Katherine.
We just want to know where Jenny is.
She says she needs my help about Jenny.
Why does she think I know where Jenny is??
You and Jesse were together last night.
She’s asking if Jesse and I were together last night…
Maybe it’s your chance! Tell her the truth!
Just tell her no and you’re sorry and you hope they find Jenny.
I’m so sorry about Jenny. I hope they find her soon.
I hope so too. For your sake as well as mine.
You and Jesse were together last night?
Why do you keep asking me that?
That’s what he told the police.
Jesse’s got something to do with it.
And if you were together, so do you.
